OL,3,CSudan militia leader convicted by the
OL,4,CICC of war crimes during Darfur war
OL,6,FDuring the trial, judges heard from 56
OL,7,Fwitnesses who described horrific
OL,8,Fviolence and the use of rape as a
OL,9,Fweapon to terrorise and humiliate
OL,10,Fwomen. One witness said that during
OL,11,Fone massacre, Abd-Al-Rahman allegedly
OL,12,Ftold fighters: "Repeat, repeat for
OL,13,Fthese people. Maybe there are some
OL,14,Fthat you have missed."
OL,16,FDefence lawyers called 17 witnesses
OL,17,Fand argued that Abd-Al-Rahman was not
OL,18,Fa militia leader, but rather "a no
OL,19,Fone" who had no involvement in the
OL,20,FDarfur conflict.
